        "kind": "pull_request",
        "title": "fix(exec-approval): stop misattributing Allow Always unavailability to policy",
        "body": "## What Problem This Solves\n\nFixes an issue where users running a command with a shell redirect (e.g. `openclaw --version 2>&1`) under `ask=on-miss` would see the approval prompt say **\"The effective approval policy requires approval every time, so Allow Always is unavailable.\"** That is false: the same command without `2>&1` *does* offer Allow Always, so the policy is not \"always\". The real reason is the command is non-persistable (runtime shell payload → one-shot), but the message wrongly blamed the policy, confusing operators into thinking their config required per-command approval.\n\nAffected surface: exec approval prompts across all channels (chat reply, native forwarder, plugin reaction runtime, exec runtime, gateway server-method, Web UI).\n\n## Why This Change Was Made\n\nThe Allow Always option is correctly dropped in two distinct cases — (a) policy `ask=always`, and (b) the specific command is non-persistable/one-shot — but a single message hard-asserted case (a). Rather than thread a reason string through every surface, the message is reworded to be reason-neutral and truthful in both cases: **\"Allow Always is unavailable for this command.\"** No behavioral/decision logic changes.\n\n## User Impact\n\nOperators no longer get a misleading claim that their approval policy requires approval every time when they merely piped/redirected a command. The prompt now states the accurate, command-scoped fact.\n\n## Evidence\n\n**Behavior addressed:** `openclaw --version` offered Allow Always; `openclaw --version 2>&1` hid it and printed the policy-blaming text (per #97069).\n\n**Before (origin/main ff1e7e13):**\n`\"The effective approval policy requires approval every time, so Allow Always is unavailable.\"`\n\n**After (this branch):**\n`\"Allow Always is unavailable for this command.\"`\n\n**Real setup tested:** built tree at commit ff1e7e13, full `pnpm install`, vitest on every approval surface touched.\n\n**Exact commands run after this patch:**\n```\npnpm vitest run src/infra/exec-approval-reply.test.ts src/infra/exec-approval-forwarder.test.ts src/plugin-sdk/approval-reaction-runtime.test.ts ui/src/ui/views/exec-approval.test.ts\npnpm vitest run src/agents/bash-tools.exec.approval-id.test.ts src/agents/bash-tools.exec-runtime.test.ts\npnpm vitest run src/gateway/server-methods/server-methods.test.ts -t \"allow-always\"\npnpm tsgo:core ; npx oxlint <6 changed files>\n```\n\n**Observed result after fix:** 80 + 128 + 3 tests pass; tsgo:core exit 0; oxlint 0 warnings/0 errors. All six emit-sites and the en.ts locale now share the neutral wording.\n\n**Not tested:** non-English locale strings retain prior translations until the next i18n sync (intentional); no visual UI screenshot (string-only change).\n\nCloses #97069",
        "branch": "fix/approval-allow-always-message",
